df_summ_trait_change_obs <- summ_change(df_trait_change_obs, option = "obs")

Overall, the 12 observational sites had significant increases in temperature trait (0.0138 C yr-1) and significant decreases in precipitation trait (2.52 mm yr-1) over the years.

By site, 8 out of the 12 sites had significant increases in temperature trait and significant decreases in precipitation trait over the years. Among all 12 sites, the temperature traits increases at a rate ranging from -0.0112 C yr-1 to 0.0633 C yr-1; the precipitation trait decreases at a rate ranging from -0.484 mm yr-1 to 7.3 mm yr-1.

Comparing warming plots to ambient plots, pooling data from all years in each phase, no significant difference was detected in Phase I or II, whereas Phase III exhibited a significant increase in temperature trait of -0.126 C and a significant decrease in precipitation trait of -14.1406135 mm.

df_summ_index_change_obs <- summ_change(df_index_change_obs, option = "obs")

Overall, the 12 observational sites had significant thermophilization (increases in CTI) (0.014 C yr-1) and significant xerophilization (decreases in CPI) (2.57 mm yr-1) over the years.

By site, 8 out of the 12 sites had significant increases in CTI and significant decreases in CPI over the years. Among all 12 sites, the mean thermophilization rate (increasing CTI per year) ranged from -0.0111 C yr-1 to 0.0633 C yr-1; the mean xerophilization rate (decreasing CPI per year) ranged from -0.2 mm yr-1 to 7.3 mm yr-1.

Comparing warming plots to ambient plots, pooling data from all years in each phase, no significant difference was detected in Phase I or II, whereas Phase III exhibited a significant thermophilization (increase in CTI) of -0.148 C and a significant decrease in precipitation trait of -17.3 mm.

Synthesize coupled CTI CPI change

dat_shift <- calc_community_shift(dat_index = dat_index)
gg_community_shift <- plot_community_shift(dat_shift, dat_niche)
gg_community_shift$combined

df_summ_shift_coupling <- summ_shift_coupling(dat_shift)
df_summ_shift_coupling
#> # A tibble: 4  6
#>   ratio      group         median      min    max scale_factor
#>   <chr>      <fct>          <dbl>    <dbl>  <dbl>        <dbl>
#> 1 cpi_to_cti Observation -12.3    -156.     9.94           0.1
#> 2 cpi_to_cti Experiment   -9.28    -23.8   40.1            0.1
#> 3 cti_to_cpi Observation  -0.0666   -0.124  0.222         10  
#> 4 cti_to_cpi Experiment   -0.0970   -0.128  0.223         10

A community thermophilization of 0.1 C corresponded to a xerophilization of 12.3 mm from the observations and 9.28 mm from the experiment. Likewise, a community xerophilization of 10 mm corresponded to a thermophilization of 0.0666 C from the observations and 0.097 C from the experiment.
